               <msContents>
                  <summary>Three receipts for payment of the syntaximon; each column represents a single payment, as does the entry at the bottom.  Payments are made by Aunes, son of Harthotes, through his agent Soterichos</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the verso, a document</note>
                     <note type="general">Part of a roll</note>
                     <note type="general">Recto: ends of right side of one column, one complete column, each with 6 lines: at the bottom 3 lines extend across both columns; this column dated 43/44 AD</note>
                     <note type="general">Verso: ends of right side of one column with 5 lines; one complete column with 8 lines this column dated 49/50 AD</note>
                     <note type="general">Some holes and surface abrasion</note>
                     <note type="general">Each side written in a different hand: the hand on the recto, is larger than on the verso.  Each is a rapid cursive</note>
                     <note type="local_note">Reserved to Rodney Ast, 7-06-09</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
